import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['delay'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of delay time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.barplot(x="distance", y="count", data=data, color='blue')
    chart.axvline(data['distance'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean Distance: {:.2f}'.format(data['distance'].mean()))
    chart.legend(loc='upper right')
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['route'] = data['origin'] + ' to ' + data['destination']
    route_counts = data.groupby('route')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    route_counts = route_counts.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False)
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='route', y='count', data=route_counts, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('Which routes have the highest number of flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('date')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='count', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['count'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median Count: {:.2f}'.format(data['count'].median()))
    chart.legend()
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = pd.to_numeric(data['count'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination'])['count'].sum().reset_index()
    pivot = data.pivot('origin', 'destination', 'count')
    sns.heatmap(pivot, cmap='YlGnBu')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight counts by origin and destination?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
